Inconsistencies & Notes

1.	Story 10 Dependency (Navigation):
	•	Story 10 (just implemented) prepared navigation to /emotions/edit and /emotions/:id/edit routes
	•	Story 10 handles missing routes gracefully (shows "Coming soon" message)
	•	Story 11 implements these routes, so navigation from Story 10 will work automatically
	•	No inconsistency – Story 10 was forward-looking, Story 11 completes the implementation

2.	Route Configuration:
	•	Story 11 adds routes to router/index.ts
	•	Routes follow the same pattern as journal editor routes (/journal/edit and /journal/:id/edit)
	•	No inconsistency – routes are added when the editor component is created (standard pattern)

3.	AppShell Back Button:
	•	AppShell currently only handles journal editor routes for back button
	•	Story 11 extends AppShell to also handle emotion editor routes
	•	This is consistent with the pattern – AppShell should handle all editor routes
	•	No inconsistency – Story 11 extends existing functionality appropriately

4.	Component Pattern Consistency:
	•	Story 11 follows the same pattern as Story 7 (JournalEditorView):
		•	Same layout structure (container, sections, action buttons)
		•	Same loading state management
		•	Same error handling pattern
		•	Same store integration pattern
		•	Same validation approach (but different validation rules)
	•	No inconsistency – Story 11 follows established patterns

5.	Validation Requirements:
	•	Emotion logs require at least one emotion (different from journal entries)
	•	Story 11 implements validation in the component (before calling store)
	•	Story 9 also validates in the store (defense in depth)
	•	No inconsistency – validation at both layers is appropriate

6.	Store Pattern Consistency:
	•	Story 11 uses useEmotionLogStore (from Story 9) for CRUD operations
	•	Story 11 uses useEmotionStore and useTagStore (from Stories 1 and 2) for data loading
	•	This matches the pattern used in JournalEditorView
	•	No inconsistency – store usage is consistent

7.	Component Reusability:
	•	Story 11 uses EmotionSelector and TagInput components (from Stories 3 and 4)
	•	These components are already tested and working
	•	Story 11 doesn't modify these components, only uses them
	•	No inconsistency – components are reused appropriately

8.	Timestamp Display:
	•	Story 11 uses formatEntryDate() utility (same as JournalEditorView)
	•	Create mode shows current date/time (same formatting logic as JournalEditorView)
	•	Edit mode shows log's createdAt (using formatEntryDate)
	•	No inconsistency – timestamp formatting is consistent

9.	Optional Fields Handling:
	•	EmotionLog interface has optional fields: note?, peopleTagIds?, contextTagIds?
	•	Story 11 handles these optional fields correctly:
		•	Empty strings become undefined
		•	Empty arrays become undefined
		•	This matches the interface definition and Story 9's expectations
	•	No inconsistency – optional fields are handled correctly

10.	Payload Preparation:
	•	Story 11 prepares payload with optional fields as undefined (not empty arrays/strings)
	•	This matches Story 9's createLog/updateLog expectations
	•	No inconsistency – payload format is correct

11.	Error Handling Pattern:
	•	Story 11 handles errors the same way as JournalEditorView:
		•	Loading errors: Show via AppSnackbar, navigate back if needed
		•	Save errors: Show via AppSnackbar, don't navigate
		•	Validation errors: Show via AppSnackbar, prevent save
	•	No inconsistency – error handling is consistent

12.	Navigation Pattern:
	•	Story 11 navigates to /emotions after successful save (same as JournalEditorView navigates to /journal)
	•	Story 11 navigates to /emotions on cancel (same as JournalEditorView)
	•	No inconsistency – navigation patterns are consistent

13.	Loading Strategy:
	•	Story 11 loads stores on mount (emotions, tags) if needed
	•	Story 11 loads log data on mount (edit mode only)
	•	This matches the pattern used in JournalEditorView
	•	No inconsistency – loading strategy is consistent

14.	Success Feedback:
	•	Story 11 shows success message after save (same as JournalEditorView)
	•	Story 11 navigates after successful save (same as JournalEditorView)
	•	No inconsistency – success feedback is consistent

15.	Component Structure:
	•	Story 11 uses AppShell (same as all views)
	•	Story 11 uses AppButton, AppSnackbar (same as JournalEditorView)
	•	Story 11 uses EmotionSelector, TagInput (same as JournalEditorView)
	•	No inconsistency – component structure is consistent

16.	Type Safety:
	•	TypeScript should ensure type safety throughout:
		•	EmotionLog type matches the interface from Story 9
		•	Store methods use correct types
		•	Component props and emits use correct types
	•	No type assertions or `any` types should be needed
	•	If type errors occur, they should be resolved by properly typing the interfaces and methods

17.	Future Integration:
	•	Story 11 completes the emotion logging feature (Stories 9, 10, 11)
	•	Story 12 (Comprehensive Testing) will add integration tests
	•	The separation is clean: Stories 9-11 = feature implementation, Story 12 = comprehensive testing
	•	No inconsistency – stories are well-separated

18.	Accessibility Considerations:
	•	Story 11 follows accessibility best practices:
		•	Form fields have proper labels
		•	Required fields are clearly marked
		•	Error messages are announced
		•	Loading states are announced
		•	Keyboard navigation works
	•	This matches the accessibility approach used in JournalEditorView
	•	No inconsistency – accessibility is handled consistently

19.	Performance Considerations:
	•	Story 11 loads stores and resolves IDs to names (same as JournalEditorView)
		•	Since stores are in-memory arrays, lookups are fast
		•	If performance becomes an issue, we could memoize resolved names, but this is not needed for initial implementation
	•	This matches the performance approach used in JournalEditorView
	•	No inconsistency – performance considerations are consistent

20.	Consistency Check with Recent Changes:
	•	Verification that Story 11 aligns with current codebase state:
		•	EmotionLog interface exists in src/domain/emotionLog.ts ✓
		•	useEmotionLogStore exists with createLog/updateLog actions ✓
		•	EmotionSelector component exists and works ✓
		•	TagInput component exists and works ✓
